The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of approximation algorithms and time-windows suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on graphs and optimization suggests that it could also belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.RO (Robotics).
